        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "First, separate the objects. The oscillating carrier has identifiable crests. The smooth envelope sets where the probability density is concentrated. They need not travel together.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.67,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "estimated_duration_s": 7,
      "narration_text": "Which speed follows the particle: the speed of a crest, or the speed of the packet that contains it?",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 5.46,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "A crest is a point of constant phase. From k x minus omega t equals a constant, its speed is omega over k. That is the phase velocity.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.3,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "For a nonrelativistic free particle, omega equals h bar k squared over two m. Divide by k, and the phase velocity is h bar k over two m, or p over two m.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.2,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The envelope comes from interference among nearby wave numbers. Its speed is the slope d omega over d k, called the group velocity.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "group"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.49,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Differentiate the same quadratic dispersion relation. The group velocity is h bar k over m, or p over m: exactly twice the phase velocity.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "derive"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.83,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "So the envelope moves ahead faster than any marked crest. In the packet's frame, crests enter through the front, drift backward across the envelope, and disappear through the rear.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "trace"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.6,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B08.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "That direction matters. If the packet outruns the crests, a crest cannot be born at the back and die at the front. The original source card had that movie reversed.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "reverse"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.9,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B09.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "The group velocity equals p over m, the classical free-particle speed and the rate at which the packet center moves. A position detector follows the probability envelope, not a carrier crest.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "map"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.18,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B10.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "Do not turn that into a universal factor of two. It follows from the quadratic nonrelativistic dispersion relation. A different omega of k gives a different relationship.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.26,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B11.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T15:16:39"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8,
      "narration_text": "One packet, two velocities. Crests move at p over two m. The envelope and its probability center move at p over m. The packet is twice as fast.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "CARD",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.9,
